column5: Katrine is around Kearney right?  I'll be out Tuesday and Saturday and/or Sunday, then that'll be it for my ice season.
Katrine is around Kearney right? I'll be out Tuesday and Saturday and/or Sunday, then that'll be it for my ice season.  Yes. Doe Lake.
Yes. Doe Lake. I had an ice hut on Big Doe Lake for years  Parents lived in Kearney
It was 17 here this morning on the Friendly Scale, don't think it got that low all January

-27 here over night. The ole Honda complained when I started her this AM. Probably should have plugged it in last night. Supposed to be a string of plus temps starting next Sunday according to the weather guys.
It may not make anyone feel better but when I checked last week the wild leeks/garlic were up about an inch so that's a good sign.  Cheers

It may not make anyone feel better but when I checked last week the wild leeks/garlic were up about an inch so that's a good sign.  Cheers   I,ll be looking for fiddleheads soon. This weekend should be thier start.
It was 17 here this morning on the Friendly Scale, don't think it got that low all January It's supposed to be 17 on the real one by Mon!
But of coarse it goes from freezing windy temps to calm and +19 the DAY AFTER walleye season closes
Where does one file an official complaint. ?
ice up #2 lol  my lake went from open back to covered and 40cm of snow on the ground.
Its been silly up here as well!  Yesterday morning was cold, by midday it was sunny and + temps. By 4 it was raining. By 7 its was 40km/hr winds and snowing like a mo fo at -10????
Stop whining!!!!
yeah, but it's 'dry cold', I bet!

Crazy drive this morning on the 400 north, driving a 2wd sierra with absolutely no weight in the back, I was crawling at 40 and driving on the rumble strip to keep traction because the people at my work are cheap asses and didn't replace the tires a month ago when I asked, white knuckle drive for 20km or so that's for sure.
You make me feel like a weanie now. ?
Funny ...   woke up to a coating of the white stuff down here this morning.  More on the way for over the week-end.  Enough already
Quit whining!  LOL!  Gonna be 28C soon, then it's too hot!  But never too hot to fish!  LOL!
Oh, BTW, are you responsible for this polar vortex crap?

The Weather is the responsibility of Mother Nature, she will take you complaints. Weather is moody but does not have intelligence so it can't be stupid. So Weather would be a female.  My golf book from 3 years ago where I keep my handicap says I had 3 rounds of golf in by this date. Not this year. Going to be in the teens next week, we'll see.  28C hot? We kept the A/C at 28C in the furnace pyrometer rooms to cool off at the Blast Furnaces.
Oh, BTW, are you responsible for this polar vortex crap?  YES, Yes I am!!!!
Me too. Are you watching/listening to the masters?
Have you even seen the sun yet this year, that far north?  Our days are already longer than yours.
I'd take it. Good for ice fishing.  Spring I kinda hermit until walleye opener.
I'd be happy with plus 5.   I have a craving for some kings.
Bet the Leafs are p'oed , last game tonite and it ain't  golfing weather yet.
Subban is getting his axe chopping skills up to par
Our days are already longer than yours.   my days have always been 24 hrs . guess its so cold up there everything moves slower  even time lol
Spent Thursday sledding on 45+ cm of fresh snow and fishing on 19" of good ice from sunrise to sunset....what's not to love?
What's not to love? 45+cm and 19" of ice. I'll take Palm trees and boat drinks anyday rather than the cold.
What's not to love? 45+cm and 19" of ice. I'll take Palm trees and boat drinks anyday rather than the cold. Wimp!!!

Spent Thursday sledding on 45+ cm of fresh snow and fishing on 19" of good ice from sunrise to sunset....what's not to love?  Just got back from Katrine. I should of brought my ice gear. Dam it was cold up there this morning . Lots of snow and lakes froze still.
